
[1]maranatha

   MARANA'THA, n. The Lord comes or has come; a word used by the apostle
   Paul in expressing a curse. This word was used in anathematizing
   persons for great crimes; as much as to say, "may the Lord come quickly
   to take vengeance on thee for thy crimes."
